### DSB normalization
adt.norm <- DSBNormalizeProtein(cell_protein_matrix = adt.fil, 
                                empty_drop_matrix = adt.empty, 
                                use.isotype.control = FALSE)

denoise.counts = TRUE with use.isotype.control = FALSE is not recommended if isotype controls are available. If the raw data include isotype controls, set `denoise.counts` = TRUE `use.isotype.control` = TRUE and set `isotype.control.name.vec` to a vector of isotype control protien names from cell_protein_matrix
"calculating dsb technical component for each cell to remove cell to cell techncial noise"
